observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the agency head:
A. Require the responsible offices entrusted with inventory items to judiciously maintain stock cards and properly monitor and update the stock cards to generate a more reliable inventory report;
B. Ensure that all issuances of inventory items be supported with Requisition and Issue Slip (RIS) and regularly submit to the Municipal Accountant within five days after end of the month pursuant to Section 189 of the Government Accounting Manual for Local Government Units and require the concerned offices to submit liquidation documents to support the issuance or distribution of inventory items;
